{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":952,"text":"I want to start by doing an experiment."},{"time":4857,"text":"I'm going to play three videos\nof a rainy day."},{"time":8935,"text":"But I've replaced the audio\nof one of the videos,"},{"time":12843,"text":"and instead of the sound of rain,"},{"time":15241,"text":"I've added the sound of bacon frying."},{"time":19137,"text":"So I want you think carefully\nwhich one the clip with the bacon is."}]},{"cues":[{"time":23695,"text":"(Rain falls)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":27394,"text":"(Rain falls)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":31627,"text":"(Rain falls)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":40611,"text":"All right."},{"time":43064,"text":"Actually, I lied."},{"time":45662,"text":"They're all bacon."}]},{"cues":[{"time":46956,"text":"(Bacon sizzles)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":52276,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":57216,"text":"My point here isn't really\nto make you hungry"},{"time":60513,"text":"every time you see a rainy scene,"},{"time":62186,"text":"but it's to show that our brains\nare conditioned to embrace the lies."},{"time":68696,"text":"We're not looking for accuracy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":71754,"text":"So on the subject of deception,"},{"time":74563,"text":"I wanted to quote one\nof my favorite authors."},{"time":77950,"text":"In \"The Decay of Lying,\"\nOscar Wilde establishes the idea"},{"time":84923,"text":"that all bad art comes from copying\nnature and being realistic;"},{"time":91096,"text":"and all great art comes\nfrom lying and deceiving,"},{"time":97030,"text":"and telling beautiful, untrue things."},{"time":100087,"text":"So when you're watching a movie"},{"time":104890,"text":"and a phone rings,"},{"time":106426,"text":"it's not actually ringing."},{"time":108942,"text":"It's been added later\nin postproduction in a studio."},{"time":113220,"text":"All of the sounds you hear are fake."},{"time":116098,"text":"Everything, apart from the dialogue,"},{"time":117932,"text":"is fake."},{"time":119110,"text":"When you watch a movie and you see\na bird flapping its wings --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":122794,"text":"(Wings flap)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":126141,"text":"They haven't really recorded the bird."},{"time":128428,"text":"It sounds a lot more realistic\nif you record a sheet"},{"time":133446,"text":"or shaking kitchen gloves."}]},{"cues":[{"time":135022,"text":"(Flaps)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":138849,"text":"The burning of a cigarette up close --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":141816,"text":"(Cigarette burns)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":145351,"text":"It actually sounds a lot more authentic"},{"time":148126,"text":"if you take a small Saran Wrap ball"},{"time":150995,"text":"and release it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":152237,"text":"(A Saran Warp ball being released)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":155869,"text":"Punches?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":157296,"text":"(Punch)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":158842,"text":"Oops, let me play that again."}]},{"cues":[{"time":160798,"text":"(Punch)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":162535,"text":"That's often done by sticking\na knife in vegetables,"},{"time":166295,"text":"usually cabbage."}]},{"cues":[{"time":168661,"text":"(Cabbage stabbed with a knife)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":170788,"text":"The next one -- it's breaking bones."}]},{"cues":[{"time":173776,"text":"(Bones break)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":176670,"text":"Well, no one was really harmed."},{"time":179028,"text":"It's actually ..."},{"time":181163,"text":"breaking celery or frozen lettuce."}]},{"cues":[{"time":184442,"text":"(Breaking frozen lettuce or celery)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":186947,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":189253,"text":"Making the right sounds\nis not always as easy"},{"time":193992,"text":"as a trip to the supermarket"},{"time":195923,"text":"and going to the vegetable section."},{"time":198643,"text":"But it's often a lot more\ncomplicated than that."},{"time":201042,"text":"So let's reverse-engineer together"},{"time":204089,"text":"the creation of a sound effect."}]},{"cues":[{"time":206437,"text":"One of my favorite stories\ncomes from Frank Serafine."},{"time":209810,"text":"He's a contributor to our library,"},{"time":211685,"text":"and a great sound designer for \"Tron\"\nand \"Star Trek\" and others."},{"time":216291,"text":"He was part of the Paramount team\nthat won the Oscar for best sound"},{"time":221573,"text":"for \"The Hunt for Red October.\""},{"time":223528,"text":"In this Cold War classic, in the '90s,"},{"time":226942,"text":"they were asked to produce the sound\nof the propeller of the submarine."},{"time":231751,"text":"So they had a small problem:"},{"time":233120,"text":"they couldn't really find\na submarine in West Hollywood."},{"time":236664,"text":"So basically, what they did is,"},{"time":240346,"text":"they went to a friend's swimming pool,"},{"time":243725,"text":"and Frank performed\na cannonball, or bomba."},{"time":249069,"text":"They placed an underwater mic"},{"time":251289,"text":"and an overhead mic\noutside the swimming pool."},{"time":254089,"text":"So here's what the underwater\nmic sounds like."}]},{"cues":[{"time":257366,"text":"(Underwater plunge)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":259608,"text":"Adding the overhead mic,"},{"time":261138,"text":"it sounded a bit like this:"}]},{"cues":[{"time":263115,"text":"(Water splashes)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":265514,"text":"So now they took the sound\nand pitched it one octave down,"},{"time":269985,"text":"sort of like slowing down a record."}]},{"cues":[{"time":272850,"text":"(Water splashes at lower octave)"},{"time":275929,"text":"And then they removed\na lot of the high frequencies."}]},{"cues":[{"time":278721,"text":"(Water splashes)"},{"time":281020,"text":"And pitched it down another octave."}]},{"cues":[{"time":284314,"text":"(Water splashes at lower octave)"},{"time":286626,"text":"And then they added\na little bit of the splash"},{"time":289156,"text":"from the overhead microphone."}]},{"cues":[{"time":291464,"text":"(Water splashes)"},{"time":294653,"text":"And by looping and repeating that sound,"},{"time":297215,"text":"they got this:"}]},{"cues":[{"time":298429,"text":"(Propeller churns)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":304463,"text":"So, creativity and technology put together\nin order to create the illusion"},{"time":311015,"text":"that we're inside the submarine."}]},{"cues":[{"time":314868,"text":"But once you've created your sounds"},{"time":318253,"text":"and you've synced them to the image,"},{"time":320671,"text":"you want those sounds to live\nin the world of the story."},{"time":325397,"text":"And one the best ways to do\nthat is to add reverb."},{"time":329997,"text":"So this is the first audio tool\nI want to talk about."},{"time":333198,"text":"Reverberation, or reverb,\nis the persistence of the sound"},{"time":338344,"text":"after the original sound has ended."},{"time":340299,"text":"So it's sort of like the --"},{"time":342891,"text":"all the reflections from the materials,"},{"time":345951,"text":"the objects and the walls\naround the sound."}]},{"cues":[{"time":348862,"text":"Take, for example, the sound of a gunshot."},{"time":351098,"text":"The original sound is less\nthan half a second long."}]},{"cues":[{"time":356138,"text":"(Gunshot)"},{"time":357747,"text":"By adding reverb,"},{"time":359460,"text":"we can make it sound like\nit was recorded inside a bathroom."}]},{"cues":[{"time":363470,"text":"(Gunshot reverbs in bathroom)"},{"time":365057,"text":"Or like it was recorded\ninside a chapel or a church."}]},{"cues":[{"time":368887,"text":"(Gunshot reverbs church)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":371043,"text":"Or in a canyon."}]},{"cues":[{"time":374199,"text":"(Gunshot reverbs in canyon)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":375984,"text":"So reverb gives us a lot of information"},{"time":378661,"text":"about the space between the listener\nand the original sound source."},{"time":383615,"text":"If the sound is the taste,"},{"time":385748,"text":"then reverb is sort of like\nthe smell of the sound."}]},{"cues":[{"time":390309,"text":"But reverb can do a lot more."},{"time":392491,"text":"Listening to a sound\nwith a lot less reverberation"},{"time":396425,"text":"than the on-screen action"},{"time":398532,"text":"is going to immediately signify to us"},{"time":401576,"text":"that we're listening to a commentator,"},{"time":404243,"text":"to an objective narrator that's not\nparticipating in the on-screen action."},{"time":410471,"text":"Also, emotionally intimate\nmoments in cinema"},{"time":414686,"text":"are often heard with zero reverb,"},{"time":416657,"text":"because that's how it would sound\nif someone was speaking inside our ear."}]},{"cues":[{"time":421024,"text":"On the completely other side,"},{"time":423009,"text":"adding a lot of reverb to a voice"},{"time":425529,"text":"is going to make us think\nthat we're listening to a flashback,"},{"time":429637,"text":"or perhaps that we're inside\nthe head of a character"},{"time":433946,"text":"or that we're listening\nto the voice of God."},{"time":436446,"text":"Or, even more powerful in film,"},{"time":438732,"text":"Morgan Freeman."}]},{"cues":[{"time":440243,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":441551,"text":"So --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":442742,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":445502,"text":"But what are some other tools or hacks"},{"time":449397,"text":"that sound designers use?"},{"time":452186,"text":"Well, here's a really big one."},{"time":459901,"text":"It's silence."},{"time":461807,"text":"A few moments of silence\nis going to make us pay attention."},{"time":465881,"text":"And in the Western world,"},{"time":468345,"text":"we're not really used to verbal silences."},{"time":470492,"text":"They're considered awkward or rude."},{"time":474537,"text":"So silence preceding verbal communication"},{"time":479021,"text":"can create a lot of tension."},{"time":481105,"text":"But imagine a really big Hollywood movie,"},{"time":484834,"text":"where it's full of explosions\nand automatic guns."},{"time":490389,"text":"Loud stops being loud\nanymore, after a while."},{"time":494008,"text":"So in a yin-yang way,"},{"time":495976,"text":"silence needs loudness\nand loudness needs silence"},{"time":499137,"text":"for either of them to have any effect."}]},{"cues":[{"time":502350,"text":"But what does silence mean?"},{"time":503751,"text":"Well, it depends how\nit's used in each film."},{"time":507416,"text":"Silence can place us inside\nthe head of a character"},{"time":510619,"text":"or provoke thought."},{"time":512261,"text":"We often relate silences with ..."},{"time":516654,"text":"contemplation,"},{"time":518558,"text":"meditation,"},{"time":521185,"text":"being deep in thought."},{"time":524569,"text":"But apart from having one meaning,"},{"time":527695,"text":"silence becomes a blank canvas"},{"time":529889,"text":"upon which the viewer is invited\nto the paint their own thoughts."}]},{"cues":[{"time":534962,"text":"But I want to make it clear:\nthere is no such thing as silence."},{"time":539192,"text":"And I know this sounds like the most\npretentious TED Talk statement ever."},{"time":544835,"text":"But even if you were to enter\na room with zero reverberation"},{"time":550164,"text":"and zero external sounds,"},{"time":552253,"text":"you would still be able to hear\nthe pumping of your own blood."},{"time":556004,"text":"And in cinema, traditionally,\nthere was never a silent moment"},{"time":560345,"text":"because of the sound of the projector."},{"time":562716,"text":"And even in today's Dolby world,"},{"time":566034,"text":"there's not really any moment of silence\nif you listen around you."},{"time":570485,"text":"There's always some sort of noise."}]},{"cues":[{"time":572734,"text":"Now, since there's no such\nthing as silence,"},{"time":575685,"text":"what do filmmakers\nand sound designers use?"},{"time":579280,"text":"Well, as a synonym,\nthey often use ambiences."},{"time":584307,"text":"Ambiences are the unique background sounds"},{"time":588200,"text":"that are specific to each location."},{"time":591272,"text":"Each location has a unique sound,"},{"time":593145,"text":"and each room has a unique sound,"},{"time":595145,"text":"which is called room tone."},{"time":596742,"text":"So here's a recording\nof a market in Morocco."}]},{"cues":[{"time":599189,"text":"(Voices, music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":605470,"text":"And here's a recording\nof Times Square in New York."}]},{"cues":[{"time":608843,"text":"(Traffic sounds, car horns, voices)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":615449,"text":"Room tone is the addition of all\nthe noises inside the room:"},{"time":619095,"text":"the ventilation, the heating, the fridge."},{"time":621508,"text":"Here's a recording\nof my apartment in Brooklyn."}]},{"cues":[{"time":624443,"text":"(You can hear the ventilation, the boiler,\nthe fridge and street traffic)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":635422,"text":"Ambiences work in a most primal way."},{"time":640718,"text":"They can speak directly\nto our brain subconsciously."},{"time":644538,"text":"So, birds chirping outside your window\nmay indicate normality,"},{"time":650937,"text":"perhaps because, as a species,"},{"time":653752,"text":"we've been used to that sound\nevery morning for millions of years."}]},{"cues":[{"time":658360,"text":"(Birds chirp)"},{"time":665839,"text":"On the other hand, industrial sounds\nhave been introduced to us"},{"time":669504,"text":"a little more recently."},{"time":671969,"text":"Even though I really like\nthem personally --"},{"time":674051,"text":"they've been used by one\nof my heroes, David Lynch,"},{"time":676488,"text":"and his sound designer, Alan Splet --"},{"time":678447,"text":"industrial sounds often carry\nnegative connotations."}]},{"cues":[{"time":681033,"text":"(Machine noises)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":688092,"text":"Now, sound effects can tap\ninto our emotional memory."},{"time":694869,"text":"Occasionally, they can be so significant"},{"time":697250,"text":"that they become a character in a movie."},{"time":700569,"text":"The sound of thunder may indicate\ndivine intervention or anger."}]},{"cues":[{"time":706373,"text":"(Thunder)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":711957,"text":"Church bells can remind us\nof the passing of time,"},{"time":715956,"text":"or perhaps our own mortality."}]},{"cues":[{"time":719827,"text":"(Bells ring)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":727773,"text":"And breaking of glass can\nindicate the end of a relationship"},{"time":732287,"text":"or a friendship."}]},{"cues":[{"time":734390,"text":"(Glass breaks)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":736788,"text":"Scientists believe that dissonant sounds,"},{"time":740365,"text":"for example, brass or wind\ninstruments played very loud,"},{"time":746438,"text":"may remind us of animal howls in nature"},{"time":750906,"text":"and therefore create a sense\nof irritation or fear."}]},{"cues":[{"time":754506,"text":"(Brass and wind instruments play)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":760714,"text":"So now we've spoken\nabout on-screen sounds."},{"time":764298,"text":"But occasionally, the source\nof a sound cannot be seen."},{"time":768955,"text":"That's what we call offscreen sounds,"},{"time":771503,"text":"or \"acousmatic.\""},{"time":773641,"text":"Acousmatic sounds --"},{"time":775887,"text":"well, the term \"acousmatic\" comes\nfrom Pythagoras in ancient Greece,"},{"time":780944,"text":"who used to teach behind\na veil or curtain for years,"},{"time":784559,"text":"not revealing himself to his disciples."},{"time":787773,"text":"I think the mathematician\nand philosopher thought that,"},{"time":791727,"text":"in that way,"},{"time":793584,"text":"his students might focus\nmore on the voice,"},{"time":797645,"text":"and his words and its meaning,"},{"time":799633,"text":"rather than the visual of him speaking."},{"time":802827,"text":"So sort of like the Wizard of Oz,"},{"time":805550,"text":"or \"1984's\" Big Brother,"},{"time":810388,"text":"separating the voice from its source,"},{"time":813678,"text":"separating cause and effect"},{"time":816379,"text":"sort of creates a sense\nof ubiquity or panopticism,"},{"time":820198,"text":"and therefore, authority."}]},{"cues":[{"time":823156,"text":"There's a strong tradition\nof acousmatic sound."},{"time":827129,"text":"Nuns in monasteries in Rome and Venice\nused to sing in rooms"},{"time":833763,"text":"up in galleries close to the ceiling,"},{"time":837646,"text":"creating the illusion that we're listening\nto angels up in the sky."},{"time":842390,"text":"Richard Wagner famously\ncreated the hidden orchestra"},{"time":846104,"text":"that was placed in a pit\nbetween the stage and the audience."},{"time":849964,"text":"And one of my heroes, Aphex Twin,\nfamously hid in dark corners of clubs."}]},{"cues":[{"time":855420,"text":"I think what all these masters knew\nis that by hiding the source,"},{"time":860187,"text":"you create a sense of mystery."},{"time":861874,"text":"This has been seen\nin cinema over and over,"},{"time":863967,"text":"with Hitchcock,\nand Ridley Scott in \"Alien.\""},{"time":867071,"text":"Hearing a sound without knowing its source"},{"time":869487,"text":"is going to create some sort of tension."},{"time":874530,"text":"Also, it can minimize certain visual\nrestrictions that directors have"},{"time":880168,"text":"and can show something\nthat wasn't there during filming."},{"time":883882,"text":"And if all this sounds\na little theoretical,"},{"time":885991,"text":"I wanted to play a little video."}]},{"cues":[{"time":889289,"text":"(Toy squeaks)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":892383,"text":"(Typewriter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":895761,"text":"(Drums)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":899164,"text":"(Ping-pong)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":902484,"text":"(Knives being sharpened)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":905786,"text":"(Record scratches)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":909405,"text":"(Saw cuts)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":910615,"text":"(Woman screams)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":912663,"text":"What I'm sort of trying\nto demonstrate with these tools"},{"time":917930,"text":"is that sound is a language."},{"time":920516,"text":"It can trick us by transporting\nus geographically;"},{"time":924571,"text":"it can change the mood;"},{"time":926579,"text":"it can set the pace;"},{"time":929482,"text":"it can make us laugh\nor it can make us scared."}]},{"cues":[{"time":934698,"text":"On a personal level, I fell\nin love with that language"},{"time":938072,"text":"a few years ago,"},{"time":939413,"text":"and somehow managed to make it\ninto some sort of profession."},{"time":945274,"text":"And I think with our work\nthrough the sound library,"},{"time":948524,"text":"we're trying to kind of expand\nthe vocabulary of that language."},{"time":955797,"text":"And in that way, we want\nto offer the right tools"},{"time":959303,"text":"to sound designers,"},{"time":960967,"text":"filmmakers,"},{"time":962339,"text":"and video game and app designers,"},{"time":964748,"text":"to keep telling even better stories"},{"time":968382,"text":"and creating even more beautiful lies."}]},{"cues":[{"time":971138,"text":"So thanks for listening."}]},{"cues":[{"time":972449,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}